        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 7:17PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 717 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles northeast of Monroe, or 4 miles east of Unionville, moving
northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fairview In Union County, Midland, Unionville, New Salem, and
Wingate.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
